				<h1>Property Taxes</h1>
					
				<p>Here's some general information about property taxes in North Carolina. If you'd like to know more, contact your local property tax office or the Property Tax Division at (919) 733-7711.</p>

				<ul class="whylist">
					<li class="why">The property tax in North Carolina is a locally assessed tax collected by each county. The North Carolina Department of Revenue doesn't send property tax bills or collect property taxes.</li>
					<li class="why">January 1 is the tax lien date.</li>
					<li class="why">Under North Carolina General Statute 105-289, The Department of Revenue is charged with the duty to exercise general and specific supervision over the valuation and taxation of property by taxing units throughout the State.</li>
					<li class="why">The Property Tax Division of the North Carolina Department of Revenue is the division responsible for this administration.</li>
				</ul>
				
